58
00:03:20,243 --> 00:03:27,390
[SPEAKER_31]: We don't have any report of subcommittees tonight and I'm going to turn it over to the superintendent to take us through our Mustang moment.

59
00:03:29,672 --> 00:03:30,132
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you.

60
00:03:30,392 --> 00:03:31,313
[SPEAKER_14]: Good evening everybody.

61
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:36,878
[SPEAKER_14]: I always start by saying this is my favorite section of the school committee meetings.

62
00:03:36,978 --> 00:03:43,183
[SPEAKER_14]: I love being able to start centering our meetings with the voices of our students.

63
00:03:43,303 --> 00:03:46,847
[SPEAKER_14]: So, this evening we are going to start, I'm going to welcome up our

64
00:03:47,407 --> 00:03:49,468
[SPEAKER_14]: world language director.

65
00:03:49,908 --> 00:04:01,170
[SPEAKER_14]: She is going to talk through lots of accolades for the world language department, as well as once she does some framing, you will hear from the voices of some of our world language students.

66
00:04:02,831 --> 00:04:03,531
[SPEAKER_14]: Medford High School?

67
00:04:04,371 --> 00:04:05,591
[SPEAKER_14]: Is it also the middle schools?

68
00:04:05,631 --> 00:04:06,271
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm so sorry.

69
00:04:06,892 --> 00:04:08,692
[SPEAKER_14]: Yes, from our secondary students.

70
00:04:10,172 --> 00:04:10,993
[SPEAKER_14]: Please come on up.

71
00:04:12,193 --> 00:04:12,613
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you.

72
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,479
[SPEAKER_14]: Would you just start with an introduction?

73
00:04:21,099 --> 00:04:21,360
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes.

74
00:04:21,460 --> 00:04:21,740
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you.

75
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:23,420
[SPEAKER_08]: Can I do a brief introduction?

76
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:23,500
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes.

77
00:04:23,620 --> 00:04:24,160
[SPEAKER_08]: Very brief.

78
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:24,840
[SPEAKER_08]: I promise.

79
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:25,621
[SPEAKER_08]: I will try.

80
00:04:26,521 --> 00:04:27,041
[SPEAKER_08]: Good evening.

81
00:04:27,061 --> 00:04:36,543
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm Katia Martigorena, Medford World Language Director, and I'm joined this evening by Chelsea McNiff, Director of English Learning Department, and some of our World Language Department members.

82
00:04:37,263 --> 00:04:48,726
[SPEAKER_08]: As we come together in this great celebration, we are passionate about helping students develop not only language skills, but also global awareness and cultural understanding, and we are proud to be part of this celebration.

83
00:04:49,826 --> 00:04:55,468
[SPEAKER_08]: It is my pleasure to introduce the World Language Department and the English Learning Department during this must-end moment.

84
00:04:55,848 --> 00:05:04,952
[SPEAKER_08]: Our students have achieved remarkable success this year, earning numerous distinctions, including LUC, Biliteracy Achievement, and the State Seal of Biliteracy.

85
00:05:05,532 --> 00:05:10,994
[SPEAKER_08]: These accomplishments reflect not only their proficiency in language, but also their deep understanding of culture.

86
00:05:11,674 --> 00:05:19,756
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm especially proud to present a group of our students from different grade levels who have earned these honors and will share their language learning journeys.

87
00:05:20,176 --> 00:05:29,158
[SPEAKER_08]: They will reflect on two important questions, why learning a language matters for students in our school and how it is shaping their life now and into their future.

88
00:05:29,638 --> 00:05:36,019
[SPEAKER_08]: Without further ado, at this time I invite our students to come here to the side and talk one by one.

89
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:37,640
[SPEAKER_08]: Can I have all the students please?

90
00:05:38,665 --> 00:05:39,165
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you.

91
00:05:39,465 --> 00:05:41,146
[SPEAKER_08]: In any order, we can just line up here.

92
00:05:41,187 --> 00:05:49,972
[SPEAKER_08]: We can go back one by one.

93
00:05:51,473 --> 00:05:51,793
[SPEAKER_17]: Ciao.

94
00:05:51,873 --> 00:05:53,454
[SPEAKER_17]: Mi chiamo Carissa Pirafore.

95
00:05:53,914 --> 00:05:56,235
[SPEAKER_17]: Sono una studenta della Medford High.

96
00:05:56,756 --> 00:05:59,978
[SPEAKER_17]: E studio l'italiano da circa dieci anni.

97
00:06:00,818 --> 00:06:01,138
[SPEAKER_17]: Hello.

98
00:06:01,218 --> 00:06:02,519
[SPEAKER_17]: My name is Carissa Pirafore.

99
00:06:02,619 --> 00:06:06,622
[SPEAKER_17]: I'm a student from Medford High, and I've been studying Italian for about 10 years.

100
00:06:07,685 --> 00:06:13,672
[SPEAKER_17]: So I believe learning another language is truly one of the most valuable opportunities I've been given in my educational career.

101
00:06:14,152 --> 00:06:19,578
[SPEAKER_17]: It is extremely important for the students in our school to take part in this opportunity because it truly does give you an upper hand.

102
00:06:20,058 --> 00:06:28,508
[SPEAKER_17]: Not only is it a very strong mental skill to have, but it does open many doors for future job opportunities in our diverse society, as well as new travel experiences.

103
00:06:30,069 --> 00:06:35,775
[SPEAKER_17]: When I began studying Italian 10 years ago in elementary school, I had no idea the huge impact it would have on my life today.

104
00:06:36,436 --> 00:06:43,783
[SPEAKER_17]: Now as a senior, I've recently had the very unique opportunity to travel and learn in Italy through an exchange program with a high school class from Venice.

105
00:06:44,704 --> 00:06:51,791
[SPEAKER_17]: During this trip, I learned so much about the culture, language, and geography, things that I never would have had the opportunity to learn on my own.

106
00:06:52,472 --> 00:07:00,699
[SPEAKER_17]: Yes, you can always take a nice vacation to Italy, but nothing will ever compare to the experience we had living life in this new country with an Italian family and new friends.

107
00:07:01,460 --> 00:07:06,665
[SPEAKER_17]: It helped me realize I want to return to Italy in the future and continue my studies and possibly life there someday.

108
00:07:07,265 --> 00:07:17,234
[SPEAKER_17]: Through this incredible experience, the new friends we made, laughs we shared, and countless memories, they're all unforgettable, and it never could have happened without taking this plunge into a second language in high school.

109
00:07:24,341 --> 00:07:25,721
[SPEAKER_23]: Hola, me llamo Emma.

110
00:07:25,741 --> 00:07:33,223
[SPEAKER_23]: Yo soy una estudiante de Medford High también y yo he aprendido español por muchos años.

111
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:35,064
[SPEAKER_23]: Hi, my name is Emma.

112
00:07:35,184 --> 00:07:38,965
[SPEAKER_23]: I'm also a student at Medford High and I've been learning Spanish for many years.

113
00:07:39,745 --> 00:07:44,566
[SPEAKER_23]: I started learning Spanish in sixth grade and I'm continuing to study it now.

114
00:07:45,626 --> 00:07:52,228
[SPEAKER_23]: Y como Carissa, yo también quiero estudiar español en mi futuro y viajar a un país hispanohablante.

115
00:07:52,788 --> 00:07:58,132
[SPEAKER_23]: Like Carissa, I also want to travel and study abroad in a Spanish-speaking country.

116
00:07:58,533 --> 00:08:11,623
[SPEAKER_23]: And I think that's one of the important things about learning another language is that you get to experience so many different cultures and communities and have so many more opportunities to learn and grow both as a person and learn and grow with these other communities.

117
00:08:17,728 --> 00:08:18,108
[SPEAKER_12]: Hola.

118
00:08:18,728 --> 00:08:19,409
[SPEAKER_12]: Me llamo Cooper.

119
00:08:19,449 --> 00:08:21,689
[SPEAKER_12]: Soy un estudiante de Español AP.

120
00:08:22,289 --> 00:08:25,470
[SPEAKER_12]: He aprendido Español por más de siete años.

121
00:08:26,010 --> 00:08:26,910
[SPEAKER_12]: My name is Cooper Hsu.

122
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:30,471
[SPEAKER_12]: I've been practicing Spanish at Medford High for more than seven years.

123
00:08:31,231 --> 00:08:37,173
[SPEAKER_12]: And I was just in Madrid a few days ago actually learning about global equity and stuff.

124
00:08:37,293 --> 00:08:39,053
[SPEAKER_12]: And all of the people in Madrid were

125
00:08:39,493 --> 00:08:47,743
[SPEAKER_12]: Spanish speakers and I thought it was really useful and important to use my skills that I've learned from Medford High to make connections with people from across the world.

126
00:08:48,024 --> 00:08:58,957
[SPEAKER_12]: Spanish can span into a bit of Italian and French and there are people from all these countries and that's how I built these connections that are going to sustain me for the years to come and I encourage everyone to learn a language.

127
00:09:05,612 --> 00:09:19,380
[SPEAKER_10]: Hola, me llamo Lina y yo también estoy una estudiante de AP español y personalmente creo que aprender un idioma es importante para los estudiantes de nuestra escuela porque abre la puerta a comprender diferentes culturas y perspectivas.

128
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:29,606
[SPEAKER_10]: Como alguien de origen maroqui que habla cuatro idiomas, inglés, árabe, francés y español, y que estudio en un liceo francés hace dos años, he visto el impacto de los idiomas.

129
00:09:29,946 --> 00:09:33,308
[SPEAKER_10]: Mi intercambio en España hace dos años donde viví durante dos meses

130
00:09:33,608 --> 00:09:37,650
[SPEAKER_10]: Me mostro que los idiomas crean oportunidades reales y confianza.

131
00:09:37,670 --> 00:09:40,591
[SPEAKER_10]: Hoy en día me ayuda a comunicarme y adaptarme.

132
00:09:40,911 --> 00:09:45,394
[SPEAKER_10]: Y sé que dará forma a mi futuro al ampliar mis oportunidades académicas y profesionales.

133
00:09:46,174 --> 00:09:50,596
[SPEAKER_10]: Hi everyone, my name is Lina and I'm also a student in AP Spanish.

134
00:09:51,156 --> 00:09:58,860
[SPEAKER_10]: And personally, I think that learning a language is important for students in our school because it opens the door to understanding different cultures and perspectives.

135
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:09,663
[SPEAKER_10]: As someone originally from Morocco who speaks four languages, English, Arabic, French, and Spanish, and studied in a French high school, I've seen how language builds connection.

136
00:10:09,863 --> 00:10:16,964
[SPEAKER_10]: My exchange program two years ago in Spain, where I lived for two months, showed me how language can create real opportunities and confidence.

137
00:10:17,364 --> 00:10:23,566
[SPEAKER_10]: Today, it helps me communicate, adapt, and I know it will shape my future by expanding my academic and career possibilities.

138
00:10:30,293 --> 00:10:37,107
[SPEAKER_39]: Hola, me llamo William y estoy estudiante de español por tres años ahora.

139
00:10:41,108 --> 00:10:47,370
[SPEAKER_39]: So, idiomas son muy importantes para estudiantes porque les dan una perspectiva nueva.

140
00:10:47,910 --> 00:10:53,192
[SPEAKER_39]: En las clases, no solamente aprendemos lenguas, pero sobre las culturas también.

141
00:10:53,632 --> 00:11:00,934
[SPEAKER_39]: Finalmente, es importante que estudiantes aprendan un idioma porque hay otras personas en otros lugares.

142
00:11:01,935 --> 00:11:08,897
[SPEAKER_39]: La habilidad para comunicar es uno de los más importantes en su vida.

143
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:21,603
[SPEAKER_39]: So basically, language classes in Metro High School are very important for the students because they teach not only the language, but also the perspective.

144
00:11:23,964 --> 00:11:30,586
[SPEAKER_39]: When you're learning in these classes, you're learning about other places and the culture from these places.

145
00:11:33,842 --> 00:11:43,070
[SPEAKER_39]: Segundo, aprendiendo un idioma está teniendo impacto en mi vida porque ahora entiendo más en el mundo.

146
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:51,576
[SPEAKER_39]: Tengo mi teléfono en español para practicar, pero recibo anuncios, videos, los artículos en español.

147
00:11:52,998 --> 00:11:54,739
[SPEAKER_39]: Y estoy muy

148
00:12:00,431 --> 00:12:02,255
[SPEAKER_39]: bien para mí.

149
00:12:02,436 --> 00:12:06,846
[SPEAKER_39]: En mi futuro, yo espero que continuare aprendiendo español.

150
00:12:07,299 --> 00:12:15,345
[SPEAKER_39]: La lengua me ayudare a conocer otras personas nuevas y crear otras experiencias aprendientas.

151
00:12:16,526 --> 00:12:20,870
[SPEAKER_39]: So basically, learning a language is having a very big impact on my life.

152
00:12:21,170 --> 00:12:23,552
[SPEAKER_39]: I'm learning a lot about the world in my classes.

153
00:12:24,633 --> 00:12:30,457
[SPEAKER_39]: I have my phone set to Spanish to help me learn these different languages and learn Spanish.

154
00:12:30,697 --> 00:12:34,460
[SPEAKER_39]: And while doing this, it's helping me see through different perspectives.

155
00:12:35,942 --> 00:12:44,108
[SPEAKER_39]: And in the future, I would like to continue learning this language to help myself meet new people and create new experiences.

156
00:12:51,174 --> 00:12:52,075
[SPEAKER_00]: Good evening, everyone.

157
00:12:52,936 --> 00:12:54,517
[SPEAKER_00]: My name is Fadson Ludière.

158
00:12:55,077 --> 00:12:56,359
[SPEAKER_00]: I speak French and Haitian Creole.

159
00:12:58,797 --> 00:13:08,304
[SPEAKER_00]: I believe a language is important for students because it helps us connect with other people.

160
00:13:08,824 --> 00:13:10,626
[SPEAKER_00]: It goes far beyond speaking.

161
00:13:11,286 --> 00:13:14,628
[SPEAKER_00]: It helps us with memory and everything.

162
00:13:14,989 --> 00:13:18,811
[SPEAKER_00]: I've learned stuff that I never knew that I could do.

163
00:13:19,552 --> 00:13:22,794
[SPEAKER_00]: I didn't even take French seriously until I got here.

164
00:13:23,154 --> 00:13:25,816
[SPEAKER_00]: I see how learning a language is important.

165
00:13:26,877 --> 00:13:31,600
[SPEAKER_00]: That's when I started taking my second language more importantly.

166
00:13:32,341 --> 00:13:39,565
[SPEAKER_00]: I'm so grateful to be here in Medford High, where they gave us the opportunity to learn a new language.

167
00:13:40,906 --> 00:13:50,713
[SPEAKER_00]: And I believe it is really important for students to keep learning because everyone at Medford High gave us the opportunity

168
00:13:53,043 --> 00:13:57,827
[SPEAKER_00]: work through the language with us while learning.

169
00:13:59,889 --> 00:14:07,636
[SPEAKER_00]: Right now, learning a language is helping me become more confident when I'm speaking and interact with other people.

170
00:14:09,297 --> 00:14:15,043
[SPEAKER_00]: I feel more open to meeting new people and understand different perspectives.

171
00:14:15,623 --> 00:14:16,564
[SPEAKER_00]: Learning a language

172
00:14:17,358 --> 00:14:22,421
[SPEAKER_00]: helped me see the world differently, and I'm thankful that I did that in Medford High.

173
00:14:22,882 --> 00:14:23,562
[SPEAKER_00]: Thank you so much.

174
00:14:30,426 --> 00:14:36,070
[SPEAKER_09]: Hola, me llamo Lennox, y soy un estudiante de Español 10 honores.

175
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:40,212
[SPEAKER_09]: My name is Lennox Lafleur, and I'm a student of Spanish 10 honors.

176
00:14:41,762 --> 00:14:54,929
[SPEAKER_09]: Creo que es importante para aprender un idioma nuevo porque si podemos entender más, podemos aprender más sobre el mundo.

177
00:14:55,549 --> 00:15:02,153
[SPEAKER_09]: Y si quieres viajar a otro país, es importante para aprender un poco del idioma.

178
00:15:03,388 --> 00:15:08,773
[SPEAKER_09]: I think that it's important to learn new languages, because if we learn new languages, we can understand, I guess, more about the world.

179
00:15:09,454 --> 00:15:14,318
[SPEAKER_09]: And, of course, if you want to travel around the world to other countries, it's important to know a little bit of the languages there.

180
00:15:15,399 --> 00:15:20,963
[SPEAKER_09]: Personalmente, quiero aprender español porque me gusta etimología.

181
00:15:21,384 --> 00:15:24,807
[SPEAKER_09]: Yo quiero entender los orígenes de las palabras.

182
00:15:26,863 --> 00:15:31,085
[SPEAKER_09]: Yo también quiero viajar por las Américas.

183
00:15:31,966 --> 00:15:36,328
[SPEAKER_09]: Español es un idioma muy común en las Américas.

184
00:15:46,846 --> 00:15:55,013
[SPEAKER_09]: Creo que así, aprendo español, puedo tener un tiempo muy fácil en otros países.

185
00:15:55,194 --> 00:15:59,738
[SPEAKER_09]: Personally, I like to learn Spanish because I like understanding the origins of words.

186
00:16:00,318 --> 00:16:05,723
[SPEAKER_09]: And I want to travel around the Americas, South America, North America, because I think they're pretty places.

187
00:16:06,283 --> 00:16:13,470
[SPEAKER_09]: And if I learn Spanish and I know Spanish, I can understand and experience, have a better experience in those countries and continents.

188
00:16:23,239 --> 00:16:25,922
[SPEAKER_03]: Bonsoir, je m'appelle Jayden et j'étudie le français.

189
00:16:26,863 --> 00:16:34,612
[SPEAKER_03]: Apprendre une langue est important car il laisse la porte ouverte à nouvelle façon de voir le monde.

190
00:16:35,293 --> 00:16:42,361
[SPEAKER_03]: I'm Jayden, I speak French, and learning a language is important because it opens the door to seeing the world in a new light.

191
00:16:44,569 --> 00:16:49,952
[SPEAKER_03]: There's a quote where if you speak to someone's native language, you don't just speak to their mind, you speak to their heart.

192
00:16:50,733 --> 00:16:57,937
[SPEAKER_03]: And the ability to be able to connect with someone on an intimate level, on not just speaking one language, speaking their language, is very powerful.

193
00:16:58,994 --> 00:17:05,359
[SPEAKER_03]: Pour moi, en ma communauté d'église, beaucoup de personnes parlent les hâtiens créoles et le français.

194
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:09,983
[SPEAKER_03]: A lot of people speak Haitian Creole and French in my church community, for instance.

195
00:17:10,383 --> 00:17:16,328
[SPEAKER_03]: And that ability to be able to not just speak to them in English, but also speak to them in French is integral in our ability to connect.

196
00:17:16,348 --> 00:17:21,091
[SPEAKER_03]: Because it shows caring, it shows compassion, and that's such an integral part of language.

197
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:29,955
[SPEAKER_03]: That's why I'm so grateful to have been able to study French these past four years and to continue to cultivate this language because it's really something special.

198
00:17:30,956 --> 00:17:31,197
[SPEAKER_03]: Merci.

199
00:17:39,275 --> 00:17:43,198
[SPEAKER_01]: Hi, my name is Sofia Derez and I'm an 8th grader at Andrews Middle School.

200
00:17:43,979 --> 00:17:49,302
[SPEAKER_01]: I believe learning a second language is important because it's a helpful skill for things like travel and jobs.

201
00:17:49,983 --> 00:17:52,645
[SPEAKER_01]: You also get to connect with people across different cultures.

