[SPEAKER_14]: Okay, we have one more Mustang moment.

269
00:27:52,371 --> 00:27:59,493
[SPEAKER_14]: Very happy and excited to welcome, we have third grade students from Brooks Elementary School.

270
00:28:00,514 --> 00:28:00,694
[SPEAKER_14]: Ms.

271
00:28:00,734 --> 00:28:03,074
[SPEAKER_14]: Deimos, are you doing a little framing before?

272
00:28:03,395 --> 00:28:10,757
[SPEAKER_14]: Okay, so Principal Deimos is gonna do a little framing about why a class of third grade students is here for Mustang moment.

273
00:28:11,757 --> 00:28:13,238
[SPEAKER_14]: And take it away, Principal Deimos.

274
00:28:14,059 --> 00:28:14,499
[SPEAKER_13]: Excellent.

275
00:28:14,539 --> 00:28:15,260
[SPEAKER_13]: Thank you very much.

276
00:28:16,601 --> 00:28:25,627
[SPEAKER_13]: I'd first like to just extend our heartfelt thank you to Miss Laura Branton-Green and her husband, Riley, who have been working with us at the Brooks for over 10 years now.

277
00:28:26,608 --> 00:28:27,709
[SPEAKER_13]: It's a great accomplishment.

278
00:28:27,749 --> 00:28:32,212
[SPEAKER_13]: They volunteer their time every year to come in with our third graders to work on creative writing.

279
00:28:32,713 --> 00:28:39,738
[SPEAKER_13]: And the song that you're going to hear tonight, Laura and her husband, Riley, they wrote the song with these students.

280
00:28:40,218 --> 00:28:40,879
[SPEAKER_13]: So this was

281
00:28:41,740 --> 00:28:45,747
[SPEAKER_13]: written by themselves with the help of Laura and Riley.

282
00:28:46,067 --> 00:28:50,095
[SPEAKER_13]: So I just want to let her frame it out just a little bit more for you and then we'll be on with the show with the kiddos.

283
00:28:52,847 --> 00:28:53,628
[SPEAKER_24]: Good evening, everybody.

284
00:28:53,668 --> 00:28:55,589
[SPEAKER_24]: Thank you so much for having us tonight.

285
00:28:56,610 --> 00:28:56,870
[SPEAKER_24]: As Ms.

286
00:28:56,890 --> 00:28:58,471
[SPEAKER_24]: Demos said, my name is Laura Brereton.

287
00:28:58,531 --> 00:29:01,573
[SPEAKER_24]: I'm a local singer-songwriter, teacher, musician.

288
00:29:02,394 --> 00:29:07,277
[SPEAKER_24]: And my husband and I have been doing the third grade songwriting project for about 10 years.

289
00:29:07,477 --> 00:29:13,041
[SPEAKER_24]: We started when our son, who is now about to graduate from Medford High, we started when he was in third grade.

290
00:29:14,322 --> 00:29:18,685
[SPEAKER_24]: And we piloted the program at the Brooks because that's where our school community was.

291
00:29:18,725 --> 00:29:20,026
[SPEAKER_24]: That's where our kids went to school.

292
00:29:20,826 --> 00:29:25,128
[SPEAKER_24]: Over the years, we actually have done it at the Missituck twice and at the Roberts as well.

293
00:29:25,828 --> 00:29:32,731
[SPEAKER_24]: And we had a schedule to be at the McGlynn Elementary literally the day everything shut down in 2020.

294
00:29:33,272 --> 00:29:35,212
[SPEAKER_24]: So we haven't been able to get there.

295
00:29:35,252 --> 00:29:36,533
[SPEAKER_24]: Hopefully down the road we will.

296
00:29:36,573 --> 00:29:40,915
[SPEAKER_24]: But our goal was to try to do this with every third grade in all of the district.

297
00:29:41,495 --> 00:29:41,976
[SPEAKER_24]: And as Ms.

298
00:29:41,996 --> 00:29:47,123
[SPEAKER_24]: Demos said, we come in, we work with the students to write an original song.

299
00:29:48,424 --> 00:29:51,328
[SPEAKER_24]: We try to tie it in somehow to the curriculum.

300
00:29:52,149 --> 00:29:57,296
[SPEAKER_24]: And this year, the kids actually have a really creative and interesting song topic.

301
00:29:57,876 --> 00:30:00,538
[SPEAKER_24]: It's called Medford Past, Present, and Future.

302
00:30:01,379 --> 00:30:10,545
[SPEAKER_24]: And so each verse describes how a school child would get to school depending on what part of history they were in.

303
00:30:10,705 --> 00:30:16,189
[SPEAKER_24]: So the first verse is sort of talking about what it was like in colonial times.

304
00:30:16,369 --> 00:30:18,811
[SPEAKER_24]: And then the second verse is about current day.

305
00:30:19,291 --> 00:30:23,354
[SPEAKER_24]: And then the third verse is sort of imagining what it might be like to get to school.

306
00:30:24,034 --> 00:30:29,556
[SPEAKER_24]: in the future and how students would arrive to school and what they might see on their ride to school.

307
00:30:30,517 --> 00:30:33,718
[SPEAKER_24]: And these are some lovely third graders that are gonna join us.

308
00:30:34,178 --> 00:30:39,500
[SPEAKER_24]: If you can give me just a second, I'm gonna set up the music, because we have some music that they're going to sing along to.

309
00:30:39,940 --> 00:30:44,442
[SPEAKER_24]: Again, thank you so much for having us and thank you for acknowledging the work that we're doing.

310
00:30:44,462 --> 00:30:45,002
[SPEAKER_24]: Appreciate it.

311
00:30:54,808 --> 00:31:05,277
[SPEAKER_13]: And just for a quick while we wait for Laura to set that up, I just want to say thank you to all the third grade students who've worked so hard and for the families who made tonight possible and bringing them in means a lot.

312
00:31:05,397 --> 00:31:05,818
[SPEAKER_13]: So thank you.

313
00:31:33,742 --> 00:31:43,130
[SPEAKER_24]: One thing I forgot to mention that we're sort of proud of is that we managed to get a disco beat, reggaeton, and reggae in this song, which is kind of unheard of.

314
00:32:06,532 --> 00:32:14,418
[SPEAKER_27]: Weekday mornings we walk to school, hand in hand along the dirt path.

315
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:25,827
[SPEAKER_27]: Over the river and through the woods, we see folks on a mystic river raft.

316
00:32:25,907 --> 00:32:33,814
[SPEAKER_27]: Small houses, barns, and taverns, pour a beer right through our town.

317
00:32:35,727 --> 00:32:40,028
[SPEAKER_27]: Shipyards for almonds and crackers, too.

318
00:32:40,088 --> 00:32:43,529
[SPEAKER_27]: Gypsy moths fly all around.

319
00:32:45,870 --> 00:32:49,631
[SPEAKER_27]: Past, present, and future always feels like today.

320
00:32:50,191 --> 00:32:54,792
[SPEAKER_27]: No matter how we get to school, we'll always find our way.

321
00:32:55,333 --> 00:32:59,454
[SPEAKER_27]: Past, present, and future is something we create.

322
00:33:00,254 --> 00:33:04,175
[SPEAKER_27]: Medford is our heart and home, and we are here to stay.

323
00:33:10,086 --> 00:33:13,409
[SPEAKER_27]: Weekday mornings, we go to school.

324
00:33:14,670 --> 00:33:18,032
[SPEAKER_27]: We hop in our car for a ride.

325
00:33:19,593 --> 00:33:23,817
[SPEAKER_27]: We look out the window and see our town.

326
00:33:24,317 --> 00:33:27,720
[SPEAKER_27]: All the scenery, golden high.

327
00:33:29,701 --> 00:33:33,344
[SPEAKER_27]: Play, step, park, the communal rail.

328
