[SPEAKER_31]: Hold on just one second while they turn on your microphone.

355
00:37:00,517 --> 00:37:09,470
[SPEAKER_20]: Hello, I'm Ryan Surratt, and I'm a former Brooks alumni, so it's great for the CDC to be able to work so hard on this song.

356
00:37:09,570 --> 00:37:10,532
[SPEAKER_20]: I just have a question.

357
00:37:10,932 --> 00:37:13,096
[SPEAKER_20]: How long have they been working on this?

358
00:37:24,093 --> 00:37:25,193
[SPEAKER_24]: Ryan, that's a great question.

359
00:37:25,253 --> 00:37:27,774
[SPEAKER_24]: So we started to work on this in early March.

360
00:37:28,514 --> 00:37:36,116
[SPEAKER_24]: And it took us about three weeks coming into the schools on various days to write the song and then do sort of a general recording of it.

361
00:37:36,896 --> 00:37:47,319
[SPEAKER_24]: And then once we finished all of that, my husband, Raleigh, who I'm sorry he couldn't be here tonight, but he puts it all together into a video in our home studio.

362
00:37:47,799 --> 00:37:51,740
[SPEAKER_24]: And then we're hoping it'll be ready in the next few weeks to be final project.

