375
00:41:59,056 --> 00:42:06,562
[SPEAKER_31]: The presentation will be by Andrew Mountford, Michael Clark, Annie Gladfelter, and Viviana Sanchez, but I'm going to turn it over to Dr. Galussi first.

376
00:42:08,297 --> 00:42:09,098
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you so much.

377
00:42:09,678 --> 00:42:11,780
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm really excited for this presentation this evening.

378
00:42:12,521 --> 00:42:17,946
[SPEAKER_14]: In case anyone is joining or listening to this presentation, I just want to do a small bit of framing.

379
00:42:19,127 --> 00:42:23,691
[SPEAKER_14]: The fabulous team from BASIC is also going to do a little bit, but I just wanted to ground people.

380
00:42:24,412 --> 00:42:24,933
[SPEAKER_14]: a little bit.

381
00:42:25,693 --> 00:42:43,989
[SPEAKER_14]: It's been a year from now, so our first presentation to the Medford community was in May of 2025, where Medford has historically faced high demand for after-school programming, and it was consistently outpacing the availability that we were able to provide.

382
00:42:44,549 --> 00:42:50,334
[SPEAKER_14]: And so we were not able to service a lot of our Medford families with proper after-school care.

383
00:42:51,215 --> 00:43:00,705
[SPEAKER_14]: And so there were some previous attempts to mitigate this situation, but sadly it didn't really yield much of the benefits and was not successful at all.

384
00:43:00,785 --> 00:43:09,034
[SPEAKER_14]: And so to address a lot of these systemic issues that we were hearing from the community, there are two pieces I just wanted to quickly frame.

385
00:43:09,174 --> 00:43:10,916
[SPEAKER_14]: One was we started a task force.

386
00:43:11,917 --> 00:43:28,416
[SPEAKER_14]: an after-school task force that was community-rooted and a lot of caregivers really got together to try to figure out on their own a lot of problem-solving, a lot of groundwork to try and help the situation for

387
00:43:29,067 --> 00:43:31,769
[SPEAKER_14]: that was happening in Medford for the lack of afterschool care.

388
00:43:32,389 --> 00:43:38,973
[SPEAKER_14]: This task force showed a lot of what true partnership and community service can do.

389
00:43:40,774 --> 00:43:42,275
[SPEAKER_14]: The task force met frequently.

390
00:43:44,696 --> 00:43:47,198
[SPEAKER_14]: We had regular meetings.

391
00:43:47,958 --> 00:43:52,201
[SPEAKER_14]: I really want to spend a minute to thank the task force.

392
00:43:52,221 --> 00:43:55,943
[SPEAKER_14]: We have some members from the task force, but I think it's very important

393
00:43:56,423 --> 00:44:13,707
[SPEAKER_14]: to note that this task force was comprised of caregivers, Medford administration, we had two school leaders, we also had representation from the after school staff, as well as for some of our meetings, the basic team.

394
00:44:14,107 --> 00:44:16,908
[SPEAKER_14]: So it was a true, and we had a school committee member.

395
00:44:17,588 --> 00:44:19,028
[SPEAKER_14]: So it was a true representation.

396
00:44:19,729 --> 00:44:24,650
[SPEAKER_14]: This after school task force was completely committed to expanding after school care.

397
00:44:26,243 --> 00:44:30,105
[SPEAKER_14]: They worked on their own time, so their dedication was just paramount.

398
00:44:30,965 --> 00:44:40,390
[SPEAKER_14]: We have people on the task force that don't even have children currently in after school programming, and just made a huge impact on the community.

399
00:44:40,450 --> 00:44:48,994
[SPEAKER_14]: So I do want to take a moment to recognize caregivers, Ada Guting, Ellen Rushman, Sarah Wides,

