01:36:20,048 --> 01:36:20,308
[SPEAKER_32]: Okay.

840
01:36:20,468 --> 01:36:26,233
[SPEAKER_32]: And then you were saying that the sliding scale, that falls into basically what we were seeing as surplus.

841
01:36:26,814 --> 01:36:27,014
[SPEAKER_06]: Yes.

842
01:36:27,134 --> 01:36:27,334
[SPEAKER_32]: Okay.

843
01:36:27,614 --> 01:36:27,794
[SPEAKER_06]: Yes.

844
01:36:27,874 --> 01:36:29,796
[SPEAKER_06]: Because those are really unrealized tuition dollars.

845
01:36:30,156 --> 01:36:35,981
[SPEAKER_06]: I mean, you think about the overall income available as being tuition dollars.

846
01:36:36,361 --> 01:36:41,446
[SPEAKER_06]: There are some, you know, small grants, you know, that also fund, you know, but

847
01:36:42,351 --> 01:36:46,134
[SPEAKER_06]: By and large, the majority of the revenue is coming from tuition dollars.

848
01:36:46,214 --> 01:36:54,581
[SPEAKER_06]: So any single dollar that is foregone because a family can't afford it, that is just unrealized revenue.

849
01:36:55,121 --> 01:36:55,381
[SPEAKER_32]: OK.

