1183
02:10:36,028 --> 02:10:43,949
[SPEAKER_07]: about the uneven demand of programming, that's just the reality of geographical location and the populations of our schools.

1184
02:10:43,969 --> 02:10:49,990
[SPEAKER_07]: How are we going to be ensuring, I think, just general fairness when we have that uneven demand when it comes to staffing, when it comes to communication?

1185
02:10:50,050 --> 02:11:00,252
[SPEAKER_07]: Obviously, when there's an increased number of students that are in these programs at schools where there is additional need, how do we, I think, make sure that all families feel like they're participating in the process?

1186
02:11:00,592 --> 02:11:04,893
[SPEAKER_07]: Obviously, the increased communication is a big part of that, but are we making sure that the program is

1187
02:11:05,935 --> 02:11:08,244
[SPEAKER_07]: Again, like equivalent or is it equitable across all things?

1188
02:11:08,264 --> 02:11:09,952
[SPEAKER_07]: Like what are we doing to make sure that's happening?

1189
02:11:10,841 --> 02:11:26,430
[SPEAKER_06]: Yeah, I mean, part of establishing that vision, as we talked about, is the strategic vision as the very first step in this process, is to communicate, again, kind of going back to communication, that this is our vision for programming, means that we're serving every child in the community.

1190
02:11:26,450 --> 02:11:35,295
[SPEAKER_06]: And even though we, you know, particularly, you know, Brooks is bound to feel the brunt of this, you know, more acutely next year, until we can get to full capacity for Brooks.

1191
02:11:36,016 --> 02:11:37,477
[SPEAKER_06]: I mean, the demand there is just,

1192
02:11:38,317 --> 02:11:40,899
[SPEAKER_06]: so much greater than it is at every other school.

1193
02:11:42,100 --> 02:11:57,351
[SPEAKER_06]: They're going to still feel that more than every other school will for next year, but they understand that our vision for programming is full access for every child in the program, and that means it's an inclusive

1194
02:11:58,286 --> 02:12:03,168
[SPEAKER_06]: experience for every Medford student for after, you know, for after school.

1195
02:12:03,808 --> 02:12:06,730
[SPEAKER_06]: And then our goal is to serve every family.

1196
02:12:07,190 --> 02:12:13,352
[SPEAKER_06]: So I think it comes first from just from communicating that vision and really incorporating that that is our highest value.

1197
02:12:15,093 --> 02:12:28,241
[SPEAKER_06]: I got into this field because I love how out-of-school time allows for education to play out based on student choice, based on the interests that students have and how far that they can take them.

1198
02:12:28,301 --> 02:12:34,525
[SPEAKER_06]: But over my time, decades working in this field, I've come to value access far more.

1199
02:12:34,845 --> 02:12:42,930
[SPEAKER_06]: And so building large programs that work happens to go hand-in-hand with building great programs, because you need to have one in order for the other to work.

1200
02:12:43,802 --> 02:12:47,104
[SPEAKER_06]: But that has to be forefront in our vision.

1201
02:12:47,164 --> 02:13:07,014
[SPEAKER_06]: So with the vision statement that we drafted for Medford Public Schools in what will be, you know, and that aligns with, you know, Medford already talks about, you know, inclusion and access, you know, to every resource as part of its kind of fundamental, you know, mission for the community.

1202
02:13:07,054 --> 02:13:12,737
[SPEAKER_06]: So aligning the afterschool mission with that and making that forefront is, I think, that strategy.

1203
02:13:13,849 --> 02:13:14,449
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you so much.

1204
02:13:14,469 --> 02:13:15,250
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah, of course.

1205
02:13:15,530 --> 02:13:15,850
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you.

