02:13:21,274 --> 02:13:21,634
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

1208
02:13:21,954 --> 02:13:23,575
[SPEAKER_02]: Two comments and a question.

1209
02:13:23,695 --> 02:13:29,439
[SPEAKER_02]: First, thanks for your work, especially thanks to the volunteers who invested their time for the community.

1210
02:13:30,159 --> 02:13:36,163
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, this doesn't happen without sort of this whole team coming together and a lot of work happening, and I've lost my notes.

1211
02:13:42,102 --> 02:13:46,645
[SPEAKER_02]: Second, I also am interested in taking a look at the financials, right?

1212
02:13:46,665 --> 02:13:56,712
[SPEAKER_02]: I think it's surprising to me, welcome, but also surprising to me that with just a 10% increase to rates, we can fund all these new positions, full-time positions and benefits.

1213
02:13:56,732 --> 02:14:04,418
[SPEAKER_02]: So that either seems to me we've been running a surplus for a real long time, which I understand is extremely likely as well.

1214
02:14:04,438 --> 02:14:06,660
[SPEAKER_02]: I just wanted to understand the full costing.

1215
02:14:08,541 --> 02:14:27,399
[SPEAKER_02]: So, in terms of my question, particularly at the two schools, the Brooks and the Roberts, where we're projecting to really increase the enrollment opportunity, is that because opportunities in facilities, opportunities in staffing, large wait lists in those school communities?

1216
02:14:28,265 --> 02:14:35,751
[SPEAKER_02]: And then, you know, along with that, are there any facility needs that we need to do particularly at those two sites to grow this, the resource therein?

1217
02:14:36,532 --> 02:14:40,535
[SPEAKER_02]: So I think that's my main question is, you know, why those two schools and do we need to invest in them?

1218
02:14:41,717 --> 02:14:42,057
[SPEAKER_06]: Absolutely.

1219
02:14:42,377 --> 02:14:53,661
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, I mean, to go back to your first comment about looking at the financials, you're funding these new positions partly with the increase.

1220
02:14:54,101 --> 02:15:03,443
[SPEAKER_06]: But keep in mind also that we're also funding this increase because we're going to be enrolling 150 more students than we were previously.

1221
02:15:03,524 --> 02:15:07,085
[SPEAKER_06]: So that's a huge increase in the total amount of revenue coming in.

1222
02:15:09,009 --> 02:15:17,338
[SPEAKER_06]: And there are, having done this for a number of years, there are economies of scale that you're going to realize as you increase seats.

1223
02:15:17,838 --> 02:15:24,125
[SPEAKER_06]: So you can kind of see when you dive into the financial sheet itself, there are different

1224
02:15:27,187 --> 02:15:31,228
[SPEAKER_06]: and kind of rules that you want to live by as you structure programs.

1225
02:15:31,288 --> 02:15:37,010
[SPEAKER_06]: You know, things like, you know, we ensure we don't spend more than 70% of our revenue on staff.

1226
02:15:37,230 --> 02:15:39,230
[SPEAKER_06]: So that's on our wages.

1227
02:15:40,571 --> 02:15:52,334
[SPEAKER_06]: And those are built into that kind of financial projection, that financial tool, so that we know as we scale up programs, as long as we are satisfying these rules, that it's going to continue to work.

1228
02:15:52,394 --> 02:15:54,535
[SPEAKER_06]: And again, with the tool, you can really see how it works.

1229
02:15:56,356 --> 02:15:57,617
[SPEAKER_06]: Sorry, go ahead if you had to follow up on that.

1230
02:15:58,258 --> 02:15:59,919
[SPEAKER_06]: Oh, yeah, absolutely.

1231
02:15:59,979 --> 02:16:05,483
[SPEAKER_06]: And then as far as why the Roberts and the Brooks, it's completely the weightless need.

1232
02:16:05,503 --> 02:16:15,251
