1242
02:17:18,888 --> 02:17:27,670
[SPEAKER_06]: There is a great need for having kids at that age and even into middle school in environments that are healthy and productive after school, where they can pursue their interests.

1243
02:17:28,530 --> 02:17:29,830
[SPEAKER_06]: That's our biggest program.

1244
02:17:29,910 --> 02:17:34,351
[SPEAKER_06]: And we do it largely with those same types of spaces in a bigger school.

1245
02:17:34,751 --> 02:17:35,411
[SPEAKER_06]: So they're larger.

1246
02:17:35,591 --> 02:17:37,271
[SPEAKER_06]: The cafeteria is a bigger cafeteria.

1247
02:17:37,571 --> 02:17:38,712
[SPEAKER_06]: The gym is a bigger gym.

1248
02:17:39,112 --> 02:17:40,072
[SPEAKER_06]: But we're not using

1249
02:17:41,113 --> 02:17:44,736
[SPEAKER_06]: 30 classrooms in the school to do it, even though it's serving 400 students.

1250
02:17:45,456 --> 02:17:56,886
[SPEAKER_06]: But I would say that going into that second year where you try to make the next jump for Brooks, we're probably going to have to look at additional spaces to use within the school to meet that big number, depending on how big that number is.

