02:18:36,902 --> 02:18:38,303
[SPEAKER_20]: I know a bunch of people

1263
02:18:39,243 --> 02:18:48,945
[SPEAKER_20]: And when I was in the books that went to elementary, that went to after school a lot, so it's good to see this finally getting some changes.

1264
02:18:49,345 --> 02:18:51,586
[SPEAKER_20]: I have a few questions though.

1265
02:18:52,246 --> 02:19:01,668
[SPEAKER_20]: What was the reason during this remodeling not having any conversations with the kids that were enrolled in attending the after school program?

1266
02:19:02,088 --> 02:19:08,350
[SPEAKER_20]: I just think that the program focuses on kids, so I think that they should have an opinion on this.

1267
02:19:09,170 --> 02:19:11,331
[SPEAKER_20]: So this may be like high above them.

1268
02:19:11,391 --> 02:19:18,776
[SPEAKER_20]: They should still have like opinion on like the specialist and the schedule and yeah.

1269
02:19:24,372 --> 02:19:27,614
[SPEAKER_25]: Honestly, we didn't survey the students because we didn't have permission to.

1270
02:19:27,634 --> 02:19:29,516
[SPEAKER_25]: I think actually it's great feedback.

1271
02:19:30,256 --> 02:19:40,903
[SPEAKER_25]: If we were to do this again, you know, and we had more time, I think reaching out to families and getting permission to speak to their students directly would be a really great additional research to have for us.

1272
02:19:41,483 --> 02:19:45,586
[SPEAKER_25]: Again, we just didn't have a direct student voice because we didn't have permission to speak to those students.

1273
02:19:49,420 --> 02:19:50,381
[SPEAKER_20]: A few more questions.

1274
02:19:51,982 --> 02:20:06,693
