02:25:54,584 --> 02:26:21,482
[SPEAKER_06]: the organization itself can kind of provide enough background information so a voucher can transfer from one organization to another so that they can properly budget for and make sure the resources are being used as they're supposed to be used without relying solely on the family to meet every deadline that might not be communicated so clearly to them.

1334
02:26:21,903 --> 02:26:23,704
[SPEAKER_06]: So I would say it's not a process that's

1335
02:26:24,004 --> 02:26:26,345
[SPEAKER_06]: free of paperwork, I wish it were, but it's not.

1336
02:26:27,566 --> 02:26:42,475
[SPEAKER_06]: But I wouldn't say that I would completely move away from that if it's possible for the managing director to help families work through this process if it's one element of the whole tuition assistance available.

1337
02:26:42,815 --> 02:26:43,095
[SPEAKER_21]: Thank you.

1338
02:26:43,115 --> 02:26:48,078
[SPEAKER_21]: I also, and this is a detail we can worry about later, but I seem to remember that if you

1339
02:26:48,835 --> 02:26:50,756
[SPEAKER_21]: Did vouchers, you couldn't do sliding scale.

1340
02:26:50,816 --> 02:26:53,338
[SPEAKER_21]: And if you did sliding scale, you could not do vouchers.

1341
02:26:53,698 --> 02:26:54,258
[SPEAKER_06]: That's not the case.

1342
02:26:54,499 --> 02:26:57,060
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, I can't say what's not.

1343
02:26:57,500 --> 02:26:59,922
[SPEAKER_06]: They may have different rules for it.

1344
02:27:00,402 --> 02:27:05,525
[SPEAKER_06]: My work with vouchers is from a licensed organization.

1345
02:27:06,566 --> 02:27:11,029
[SPEAKER_06]: And Medford would have, because it's run by the public school district, would have an exemption to licensing.

1346
02:27:11,429 --> 02:27:14,351
[SPEAKER_06]: So I'm not sure if that's the case.

1347
02:27:14,591 --> 02:27:16,732
[SPEAKER_06]: That's a good question that would need to be answered for sure.

1348
02:27:16,993 --> 02:27:17,253
[SPEAKER_21]: Thank you.

1349
02:27:18,362 --> 02:27:30,967
[SPEAKER_31]: Before we go back to the students, I think Dr. Galluzzi has an add-on to the conversation about sliding scale and vouchers in terms of participation, and Member Parks has a point of information.

1350
02:27:31,088 --> 02:27:33,549
[SPEAKER_31]: So I'm going to field those two, and then we will return.

1351
02:27:33,829 --> 02:27:43,253
[SPEAKER_31]: But if you guys could keep your conversation to a minimum, it's providing feedback across the floor, and I just want to make sure we can hear the questions that are being asked.

1352
02:27:43,613 --> 02:27:43,813
[SPEAKER_31]: Thanks.

1353
02:27:47,775 --> 02:27:48,155
[SPEAKER_14]: Thank you.

1354
02:27:48,816 --> 02:27:51,977
[SPEAKER_14]: I think you, Member Rousseau, got a lot of information from Andrew.

1355
02:27:51,997 --> 02:27:54,358
[SPEAKER_14]: I think that's why we are continuing.

1356
02:27:54,558 --> 02:27:57,879
[SPEAKER_14]: And later on with the rate card, you'll see we're continuing with the sliding scale.

1357
02:27:57,959 --> 02:28:07,063
[SPEAKER_14]: But something for the managing director and our continued partnership with BASIC to explore the voucher system is something that we have for next year.

1358
02:28:08,204 --> 02:28:15,227
[SPEAKER_14]: Just a point of information for people listening and for the school committee members, currently to date,

1359
02:28:16,257 --> 02:28:23,782
[SPEAKER_14]: With the current after school program there are 54 students that are receiving some level of support through the sliding scale.

1360
02:28:24,923 --> 02:28:36,671
[SPEAKER_14]: It is about and I want to make sure that I use that word about one hundred thirty eight thousand dollars that is being funded through Medford public schools to support families in need.

1361
02:28:37,272 --> 02:28:44,657
[SPEAKER_14]: I would say that more than half of that 54 are at one particular school.

1362
02:28:45,205 --> 02:28:47,214
[SPEAKER_14]: which is the Mugglin Elementary School.

1363
02:28:49,625 --> 02:28:56,391
[SPEAKER_14]: there is a range from 20% of assistance to 100% of assistance.

1364
02:28:56,991 --> 02:29:15,186
[SPEAKER_14]: And I do also want to say that in those numbers, sometimes our students that are classified as McKinney-Vento, and so they absolutely will, and that is part of to member Olopade's question about communication, students that are

1365
02:29:16,152 --> 02:29:20,541
[SPEAKER_14]: McKinney-Vento status, or for people that don't know what that is, it's homeless.

1366
02:29:21,695 --> 02:29:40,103
[SPEAKER_14]: We will be very transparent about wait lists, but students that need after school care that are in a homeless situation will absolutely sometimes be served and provided a spot before we maybe release students from that may be on the wait list.

1367
02:29:41,024 --> 02:29:47,987
[SPEAKER_14]: But I just wanted to make sure that I gave at least some context and data to what the current landscape is for the sliding scale.

1368
02:29:49,812 --> 02:30:00,179
[SPEAKER_14]: With the increased capacity, I would say that I do anticipate that there will be more need for the sliding scale, especially at the McGlynn Elementary for sure.

