02:30:03,702 --> 02:30:04,362
[SPEAKER_32]: Member Parks.

1370
02:30:07,024 --> 02:30:10,667
[SPEAKER_32]: I just wanted to make a quick point to you, Member Russo.

1371
02:30:11,247 --> 02:30:16,111
[SPEAKER_32]: The vouchers, having used them, they were not difficult to get through.

1372
02:30:16,451 --> 02:30:19,213
[SPEAKER_32]: They took extensive period to get off of them.

1373
02:30:19,708 --> 02:30:27,734
[SPEAKER_32]: And then I remember finally getting off of them and then getting the phone call that Medford was no longer using them, which was the most disappointing phone call ever.

1374
02:30:28,915 --> 02:30:31,838
[SPEAKER_32]: But they were, it was not, it was just a lengthy process.

1375
02:30:31,918 --> 02:30:34,360
[SPEAKER_32]: It was not a difficult process at the time.

1376
02:30:34,800 --> 02:30:36,501
[SPEAKER_32]: So, and that was post COVID, so.

