02:30:41,445 --> 02:30:43,247
[SPEAKER_31]: Member Rousseau, and please be brief.

1378
02:30:44,405 --> 02:30:57,734
[SPEAKER_21]: I certainly respect, certainly that sounds terrible, but I mean for folks that are not well educated and have the space to do all of that and to wait.

1379
02:30:59,205 --> 02:31:01,366
[SPEAKER_21]: I know, but we didn't make this up.

1380
02:31:01,466 --> 02:31:08,089
[SPEAKER_21]: This was a real problem that was happening statewide, where there are lots of people who are not able to finish the process.

1381
02:31:08,649 --> 02:31:12,611
[SPEAKER_21]: And, you know, it's a couple forms, but it's a couple forms for me and you.

1382
02:31:12,691 --> 02:31:19,594
[SPEAKER_21]: It's not necessarily a couple forms for people who don't speak English or who have four jobs because rents are out of control.

1383
02:31:19,634 --> 02:31:28,538
[SPEAKER_21]: Like, I think that we didn't make that decision lightly, and so I certainly understand that, but I think that we are not

1384
02:31:29,232 --> 02:31:31,273
[SPEAKER_21]: the target audience of getting rid of the vouchers.

1385
02:31:31,313 --> 02:31:33,253
[SPEAKER_21]: So I just hope we look at that carefully.

1386
02:31:33,493 --> 02:31:33,793
[SPEAKER_21]: Thank you.

1387
02:31:39,915 --> 02:31:41,435
