[SPEAKER_32]: Member Parks.

1735
03:02:39,799 --> 03:02:52,483
[SPEAKER_32]: And maybe to that point I mean I know that the five days a week it went up $50 a month just under 10 percent for the annual.

1736
03:02:52,983 --> 03:03:05,946
[SPEAKER_32]: I know that other programs that students in the district are going to actually went up as much as 40 percent for their annual rate this past year and that

1737
03:03:08,608 --> 03:03:10,370
[SPEAKER_32]: Maybe it's a communication.

1738
03:03:10,970 --> 03:03:19,341
[SPEAKER_32]: If you are a non-renewing family, if it is because of the increase in cost, please come talk to us.

1739
03:03:19,761 --> 03:03:21,684
[SPEAKER_32]: Like just a simple statement like that.

1740
03:03:23,126 --> 03:03:26,510
[SPEAKER_32]: And just leave it as that and we can talk to you.

1741
03:03:29,763 --> 03:03:38,450
[SPEAKER_31]: If that would be I would also point out that while it's aspirational that we would approve rates before this time of year like we historically have not.

1742
03:03:38,550 --> 03:03:45,795
[SPEAKER_31]: So it's not different in a material way this year in terms of the timing of this than in my six years on the committee.

1743
03:03:46,056 --> 03:03:51,160
[SPEAKER_31]: There's many there's many years where we didn't do anything at all here.

1744
03:03:55,423 --> 03:03:56,724
[SPEAKER_14]: I believe that was summer programming.

