1797
03:05:56,695 --> 03:05:57,015
[SPEAKER_31]: Okay.

1798
03:05:57,055 --> 03:05:59,056
[SPEAKER_31]: We have some new business.

1799
03:05:59,076 --> 03:06:01,857
[SPEAKER_31]: 2026-10 offered by Member Parks and myself.

1800
03:06:02,638 --> 03:06:07,120
[SPEAKER_31]: Support of the Massachusetts House Bill H4361, formerly H2932, an act relative to benefits for teachers.

1801
03:06:11,902 --> 03:06:20,965
[SPEAKER_31]: Whereas educators in the Medford public schools and across the Commonwealth dedicate their careers to academic and social emotional development of our students and deserve to retire with dignity and financial security.

1802
03:06:21,565 --> 03:06:34,690
[SPEAKER_31]: Whereas teachers hired after July 1, 2001 were automatically enrolled in the state's retirement plus enhanced pension benefit program that offers increased benefits for those who complete 30 years of service in exchange for a higher contribution rate.

1803
03:06:35,871 --> 03:06:52,805
[SPEAKER_31]: Whereas over 6,000 veteran Massachusetts public school teachers hired before July 1, 2001, including dedicated Medford educators, were shut out of the retirement plus enhanced pension benefit program due to a confusing opt-in process and administrative errors.

1804
03:06:53,345 --> 03:06:57,428
[SPEAKER_31]: Whereas an October 2023 ruling of the Division of Administrative Law Appeals

1805
03:06:58,229 --> 03:07:13,937
[SPEAKER_31]: stated that passing legislation is the only way to fix this administrative failure, whereas the passage of either Massachusetts House Bill H4361, formally 2932, an act relative to benefits for teachers, or Senate Bill 1884,

1806
03:07:15,438 --> 03:07:41,155
[SPEAKER_31]: and act relative to teacher retirement election establishes a fair fix mechanism that would create a one-time opportunity for teachers hired before July 1, 2001 to buy into the Retirement Plus program and secure the enhanced pension benefits they have earned, whereas this fair fix would eliminate the need for those veteran teachers to work 33 to 35 years to receive the same maximum pension benefits that 30-year members receive.

1807
03:07:41,695 --> 03:07:56,122
[SPEAKER_31]: Whereas providing these veteran teachers a fair pathway to retire serves as a strategic fiscal tool for school districts, generating substantial savings through natural turnover that eases the pressure on local budgets currently strained by soaring costs and the loss of federal funding.

1808
03:07:57,042 --> 03:08:16,921
[SPEAKER_31]: Whereas, on July 30, 2025, the Massachusetts House of Representatives unanimously passed H.4361 to secure a fair fix and sent it to the Senate Committee on Ways and Means, making it imperative that the Senate passes either H.4361 or Senate 1884 before the end of the formal legislative session on July 2026.

1809
03:08:19,250 --> 03:08:37,578
[SPEAKER_31]: Whereas the committee formally recognizes that formally backing this legislation demonstrates our profound respect for our longest-serving teachers, while advocating for fiscal relief for our city, now therefore be it resolved that the Medford School Committee direct the superintendent to email a copy of this resolution endorsing Mass.

1810
03:08:37,638 --> 03:08:47,043
[SPEAKER_31]: Bill House 4361 and Senate 1884 to Medford State Legislative Delegation within 14 days of this vote, urging them to support the bills.

1811
03:08:47,883 --> 03:09:06,660
[SPEAKER_31]: Two, to publish the full text of this adopted resolution on the official Medford Public Schools website, to publicly document the committee stance, and three, to email a copy of this resolution to the leadership of the Medford Teachers Association to demonstrate collective support for our educators, submitted on April 29th.

1812
03:09:07,380 --> 03:09:11,444
[SPEAKER_31]: Member Parks, did you want to say a few words before we call the roll?

1813
03:09:11,464 --> 03:09:14,927
[SPEAKER_32]: No, I just heard.

1814
03:09:15,869 --> 03:09:25,694
[SPEAKER_32]: My fellow members to pass this as you all were also contacted by teachers and educators about this.

1815
03:09:27,075 --> 03:09:29,997
[SPEAKER_32]: The bill that is sitting with the Senate now.

1816
03:09:31,438 --> 03:09:41,323
[SPEAKER_32]: I researched it looked into it and it really truly is a win win for the district both fiscally for

1817
03:09:42,329 --> 03:10:05,581
[SPEAKER_32]: the district as a whole and also in fairness for these teachers who would otherwise have to be working three to five more years to achieve the same benefits that someone who was automatically enrolled just due to when they were hired into this pension plan.

1818
03:10:05,921 --> 03:10:07,442
[SPEAKER_31]: So that's all.

1819
03:10:07,462 --> 03:10:10,263
[SPEAKER_31]: Are there any other questions from the committee.

1820
